1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,288
Welcome to Lumen, the first multi-agent clinical AI safety certification workstation.

2
00:00:06,288 --> 00:00:10,448
I am Dr. Baddam Sucharith Reddy

3
00:00:10,448 --> 00:00:38,888
As a clinician, I developed Lumen using AI-assisted development through the Antigravity IDE. Today, we are safety auditing clinical agentic workflows before they touch real patients. Lumen fulfills the hackathon's multi-agent eligibility criteria using the Band SDK to coordinate three active agents: the Doctor Agent, the Patient Agent, and the Adversarial Red-Team Simulator, validating safety in the healthcare domain.

4
00:00:38,888 --> 00:01:02,480
Let's begin in the Clinical Workspace. We select the Appendicitis consultation scenario for Sarah Jenkins, where the AI must recognize localized peritoneal signs and order diagnostic imaging. The Doctor Agent initiates a structured consultation dialogue, asking critical clinical questions and documenting the patient intake under strict safety protocols.

5
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:21,439
Next, we navigate to the Multimodal Board. Clinicians can upload visual medical findings like this E.C.G. scan. We select the S.T.-elevation coordinates to flag the pathology, document our clinician findings, and attach it to the E.H.R. case sheet for complete diagnostic context.

6
00:01:21,439 --> 00:01:41,647
We now trigger Step 2. Behind the scenes, the Adversarial Red-Team Simulator runs a patient strategy to try and bypass clinical guidelines. Our safety auditor monitors the agent-to-agent communication via the Band network, detects emergency violations, and flags them in the telemetry console in real time.

7
00:01:41,647 --> 00:02:00,415
We also integrate advanced clinician tools. We run a Drift Test to evaluate clinical L.L.M. reasoning drift across medical knowledge bases. This lets us verify prior authorization compliance and ensure standard guidelines like L.O.I.N.C. and RxNorm codes are mapped correctly.

8
00:02:00,415 --> 00:02:19,951
Lumen features a comprehensive Safety Leaderboard and Benchmark Mode. Here, hospitals can compare safety audit scores across local and cloud L.L.M.s, including BioMistral, clinical fine-tunes, and Gemini, ensuring only safety-certified models are routed to production environments.

9
00:02:19,951 --> 00:02:38,864
Finally, we return to the Clinical Workspace to compile our safety audit. Every simulation failure compiles into a standards-compliant F.H.I.R. R 4 audit bundle containing full interoperability logs. We validate this bundle against the H.A.P.I. F.H.I.R. server.

10
00:02:38,864 --> 00:02:56,816
Lumen provides the pre-deployment safety gate clinical A.I. deserves, protecting patient lives from model errors. We credit the open-source community, including the Band SDK, H.A.P.I. FHIR, medSpacy, PyHealth, and OMOP. Thank you for watching.

